The paper deals with the satisfiability of random 2-SAT problems, which is a classic problem in computer science and falls under the category of Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also discusses the use of power-law-like distributions, which are commonly used in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Complex Systems (cs.CC) research. The configuration model used in the paper is a popular tool in Statistical Inference (cs.SI) and Network Science (cs.IT).
